answers.body_markdown:
When you start a program, all variables are stored in the RAM (quick storage). Of course they are gone once you close the app, because all of the apps data in the RAM is being deleted.

If you did not completely close the app, you probably assign a value to your variable in `onCreate()`. Whatever this value is, you should assign it directly where you declare your variable (e.g. `boolean x = true`);

`static` only means that a variable in `class X` is not a property of every instance of `X` (`new X()`), but a unique variable of that class.

What you want to do is save your data in the internal storage. For small amounts of data (up to a few thousand variables), the best way is to use `SharedPreferences`.

They use a key-value system: Each *key*, which is a `String`, is always mapped to a *value*, which can be most *primitive type*s (`boolean`, `short`, `int`, `long`, `float`) or a `String` / `Set&lt;String&gt;`.

You probably use a (class that `extends`) `AppCompatActivity`. In that, you should already have a method called `onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState)`. You will need another one of these so called *life cycle method*s called `onPause()`. This method is being called when your `AppCompatActivity` is **not** focused anymore. This happens for events like 

- leaving the app
- closing the app
- turning off the phone
- opening Google Assistent.

This is the code you need to use:

    public void onPause() {
        SharedPreferences.Editor editor = getApplicationContext().getSharedPreferences(&quot;ANY NAME&quot;, MODE_PRIVATE).edit();
        editor.putBoolean(&quot;ENTER_THE_NAME&quot;, enter_boolean_name);
        // ... you can e.g. use putInt(String, int);
        editor.commit();
    }

And to get it back:

    public void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        SharedPreferences prefs = getApplicationContext().getSharedPreferences(&quot;ANY NAME&quot;, MODE_PRIVATE);
        enter_boolean_name = prefs.getBoolean(&quot;ENTER_THE_NAME&quot;);
    }

